cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC

This paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze user predictions on social media, specifically Twitter. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and aggregation, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also touches on the topic of measuring the reliability of individual accounts, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks).
